  "text": "The Kafka consumer heartbeat session timeout is defined and checked through a chain of classes and configurations:\n\n1. CONFIGURATION DEFINITION:\nThe session timeout is configured via CommonClientConfigs.SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG (line 207 in CommonClientConfigs.java), which defines the \"session.timeout.ms\" configuration parameter used to detect client failures in group management.\n\n2. CONFIGURATION STORAGE:\nThe session timeout value is stored in GroupRebalanceConfig.sessionTimeoutMs (line 41 in GroupRebalanceConfig.java), extracted from the client configuration (line 52).\n\n3. TIMEOUT THRESHOLD INITIALIZATION:\nThe Heartbeat class (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Heartbeat.java) initializes a sessionTimer with the timeout value at line 52: `this.sessionTimer = time.timer(config.sessionTimeoutMs);`. This timer tracks when a heartbeat response should be received.\n\n4. TIMEOUT CHECKING IN POLLING LOOP:\nDuring the consumer polling loop, the AbstractCoordinator's HeartbeatThread.run() method checks if the session timeout has expired at line 1513: `else if (heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now))`. This method delegates to Heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired() (lines 119-122), which returns whether the sessionTimer has expired.\n\n5. ERROR LOGGING/RAISING:\nWhen the session timeout expires (line 1513-1517 in AbstractCoordinator.java), the HeartbeatThread calls `markCoordinatorUnknown(\"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\")`. This triggers the markCoordinatorUnknown method (lines 1004-1008), which logs an info-level message: \"Group coordinator {} is unavailable or invalid due to cause: {}. isDisconnected: {}. Rediscovery will be attempted.\" with the cause being \"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\".\n\nThe session timer is reset (Heartbeat.resetSessionTimeout(), line 131-134) whenever a successful heartbeat response is received (Heartbeat.receiveHeartbeat(), line 102), ensuring the timer only triggers if heartbeats stop arriving for the duration of sessionTimeoutMs."
}

